WEBVTT

00:01.251 --> 00:02.919
<i>Previously on</i> This Is Us...

00:03.003 --> 00:05.922
What is so terrible about me
right now?

00:06.006 --> 00:07.716
You're just different.

00:07.799 --> 00:10.301
Moving here is the only way that
we are gonna stay a family.

00:10.385 --> 00:13.138
Did you, uh, fill
Sheila's job yet?

00:13.221 --> 00:14.889
No, but we're looking
at applicants.

00:14.973 --> 00:16.933
I'd like to be considered.

00:17.976 --> 00:19.227
-BETH: Jack!
-TOBY: Jack!

00:19.310 --> 00:20.729
Jack!

00:20.812 --> 00:22.605
Jack?! Where are you?

00:23.481 --> 00:25.859
Hey. Hey, buddy.
Hey, buddy, Grandma's here.

00:25.942 --> 00:27.652
I told you to listen
for the click.

00:27.736 --> 00:29.195
Maybe I would have
heard the click

00:29.279 --> 00:31.031
if you weren't yelling
at me all the time.

00:31.114 --> 00:34.409
I don't know if Toby and I
are gonna make it.

00:34.492 --> 00:37.203
(affected):
Marriage...

00:37.287 --> 00:41.916
<i>Marriage is what brings us</i>
<i>together today.</i>

00:42.000 --> 00:43.752
Coming in, coming in,
I don't know the rules,

00:43.835 --> 00:45.754
but I gotta get something
cleared for the toast.

00:45.837 --> 00:47.505
I just need to know
if movie quotes

00:47.589 --> 00:49.341
-or impressions are allowed.
That's all.
-KATE: Yes.

00:49.424 --> 00:52.469
Yes. This is the last time
I'm doing this,

00:52.552 --> 00:54.554
so go crazy, brother.

00:56.097 --> 00:57.891
You look beautiful.

00:57.974 --> 00:59.267
Okay, get out. Get out.

00:59.351 --> 01:00.560
-Bye-bye.
-The whole thing,
it's really great.

01:00.643 --> 01:02.020
-MADISON: Bye!
-KEVIN: Oh, come on.

01:02.103 --> 01:03.563
Geez, kill a guy
for trying to deliver

01:03.646 --> 01:05.440
a perfect wedding speech!

01:05.523 --> 01:07.233
Ah, your brother's an idiot.

01:07.317 --> 01:09.194
But he's right.
You are beautiful.

01:09.277 --> 01:11.196
Philip is going to lose it.

01:11.279 --> 01:14.407
You are the perfect bride.
And this is going to be

01:14.491 --> 01:15.617
the perfect day.

01:15.700 --> 01:18.078
Beth, we both know today
will go wrong

01:18.161 --> 01:20.997
in a thousand ways,
but it doesn't matter.

01:21.081 --> 01:24.459
Kate Pearson, you are
an incredibly zen bride.

01:24.542 --> 01:26.711
Have you been hitting my CBD pen
in that dressing room?

01:26.795 --> 01:29.047
(laughs): No.

01:29.130 --> 01:31.132
(phone ringing)

01:38.723 --> 01:40.392
Hello?

01:41.434 --> 01:42.894
Hi.

01:44.813 --> 01:46.147
Hi.

01:46.231 --> 01:48.900
Um, hey, listen, I know,
I know you're getting married

01:48.983 --> 01:52.278
in a few hours.
Um, congratulations.

01:52.362 --> 01:54.781
I just, I just
wanted to say...

01:58.159 --> 02:00.662
Kate, you know what
you said to me

02:00.745 --> 02:02.288
the day we signed
our divorce papers?

02:08.670 --> 02:10.130
Yeah, I remember.

02:11.423 --> 02:13.425
I want you to know...

02:13.508 --> 02:15.844
<i>that I see it now.</i>

02:15.927 --> 02:18.930
<i>I'm sorry it took me so long.</i>

02:20.432 --> 02:22.434
If only I'd had
a crystal ball,

02:22.517 --> 02:25.270
if I could've seen the way
that this all ended up.

02:26.771 --> 02:29.482
Yeah. Life would be much simpler

02:29.566 --> 02:32.235
if we could live it
backwards, huh?

02:35.280 --> 02:37.282
♪ ♪

03:01.097 --> 03:03.475
Well, they're both sleeping in.

03:03.558 --> 03:06.061
-Small miracles.
-Yeah.

03:09.522 --> 03:12.942
I imagine Jack is pretty spent.

03:24.829 --> 03:28.458
I am going to take
the job here in L.A.

03:28.541 --> 03:31.002
The one that I turned down.

03:31.086 --> 03:32.879
It'll be a huge step back
in my career,

03:32.962 --> 03:36.758
but I'm willing to do whatever
it takes to save our family.

03:38.760 --> 03:40.553
Okay.

03:44.015 --> 03:47.894
Um, we've got to go
to couples therapy.

03:47.977 --> 03:49.688
And I know that you haven't
wanted to in the past.

03:49.771 --> 03:53.358
I'll do it. I'll do it.

03:53.441 --> 03:54.818
Whatever it takes.

04:01.199 --> 04:03.576
Whatever it takes.

04:03.660 --> 04:05.620
-You're home!
-Okay, you ready to help me?

04:05.704 --> 04:08.289
This one? Okay.
Can you hand that one to Mama?

04:08.373 --> 04:09.582
-Be careful. Careful.
-Here you go, Mama.

04:09.666 --> 04:10.583
KATE:
Oh, thank you.

04:10.667 --> 04:12.168
-TOBY: All right. Here we go.
-JACK: Yes!

04:12.252 --> 04:13.461
TOBY:
There you go.

04:13.545 --> 04:15.380
Yeah, and so Toby
was trying really hard

04:15.463 --> 04:18.049
to make San Francisco work
for all of us.

04:18.133 --> 04:19.342
I mean, killing himself
basically,

04:19.426 --> 04:22.012
coming back and forth
every weekend...

04:22.095 --> 04:25.390
A-And Kate was incredible
with the kids.

04:25.473 --> 04:28.268
She picked up so much of
the slack while I was gone.

04:29.352 --> 04:31.521
♪ ♪

04:37.152 --> 04:39.738
I hope this classroom treats you
as well as it treated me.

04:41.322 --> 04:44.034
This is for you.

04:46.119 --> 04:48.872
Now, I'm going to start
walking you through

04:48.955 --> 04:51.166
your new duties as a supervisor.

04:52.500 --> 04:56.338
-This is your office.
-TOBY: Oh. Right.

04:59.674 --> 05:01.051
Welcome aboard.

05:01.134 --> 05:03.595
Yeah, thank you.

05:08.767 --> 05:11.936
(humming)

05:16.358 --> 05:18.109
What's that song, Mama?

05:18.193 --> 05:21.237
That is a song that I'm teaching
the kiddos at school.

05:21.321 --> 05:23.114
(keys jingling)

05:23.198 --> 05:26.284
-Hey. Hey.
-Hi.

05:26.368 --> 05:29.245
-(Hailey babbles)
-How-how was your day?

05:29.329 --> 05:31.790
Oh, yeah, it was great. Yours?

05:33.541 --> 05:34.834
It was fine.

05:45.261 --> 05:46.805
I'm sure she'll be here
any minute.

05:46.888 --> 05:50.058
Traffic this time of day
can be so unpredictable.

05:50.141 --> 05:51.851
Yeah.

05:51.935 --> 05:53.687
We've been coming here
for six months.

05:53.770 --> 05:56.022
She knows how long it takes
to get here.

05:58.233 --> 06:00.276
Hi. I'm sorry I'm late.

06:00.360 --> 06:02.278
Jack's teacher cornered me
at pickup

06:02.362 --> 06:05.615
and then he guilted me
into buying the new class bird.

06:05.699 --> 06:09.327
So, anyway, um,
I did my best. Sorry.

06:09.411 --> 06:10.870
Sure you did.

06:12.122 --> 06:13.581
What is that supposed to mean?

06:16.001 --> 06:18.044
Toby, it seems like
you're having feelings

06:18.128 --> 06:20.005
about Kate being late.

06:20.088 --> 06:25.802
I'm having feelings about
Kate being late again.

06:25.885 --> 06:28.471
You know, you could be
on time if you wanted to.

06:28.555 --> 06:30.265
You don't have to spend
20 minutes

06:30.348 --> 06:34.728
talking to Jack's teacher
every time you pick him up.

06:34.811 --> 06:37.272
I am polite to our
children's teacher

06:37.355 --> 06:38.732
because the way
that I treat them

06:38.815 --> 06:40.400
impacts the way they treat him.

06:40.483 --> 06:43.028
Something you might know if
you ever spent a second longer

06:43.111 --> 06:44.404
at his school
than you have to, right?

06:44.487 --> 06:46.072
Okay. Wow.
So now I'm not

06:46.156 --> 06:47.532
spending enough time
at Jack's school?

06:47.615 --> 06:49.617
Good to know.
Another secret test

06:49.701 --> 06:52.287
about our kids that I didn't
know I was failing.

06:52.370 --> 06:54.330
I am really so tired of this.

06:54.414 --> 06:55.790
Every day

06:55.874 --> 06:57.751
it's just like a different
version of the same fight.

06:57.834 --> 06:59.878
It's like we are trapped

06:59.961 --> 07:02.589
in a hellish version of
<i>Groundhog Day.</i>

07:03.965 --> 07:06.384
Dianne, you've met a lot
of miserable couples.

07:06.468 --> 07:08.178
Some make it, some don't.

07:08.261 --> 07:11.598
In your professional opinion,
which kind are we?

07:11.681 --> 07:14.184
First, she's not
a Magic 8 Ball, Toby.

07:14.267 --> 07:17.228
Okay? And maybe if you actually
listened when we come here,

07:17.312 --> 07:18.938
we might be in a different spot,
right?

07:19.022 --> 07:20.899
-You think that.
-Okay, you know what?

07:20.982 --> 07:22.025
Screw it.

07:22.108 --> 07:24.861
You can come late,
I can leave early.

07:30.867 --> 07:32.035
(door slams)

07:37.499 --> 07:40.335
Great engagement party, guys.

07:40.418 --> 07:42.587
Have you started talking about
wedding venues yet?

07:42.671 --> 07:44.631
-Because I have thoughts.
-KATE: Yeah.

07:44.714 --> 07:46.174
We're going to Santa Ynez
next month.

07:46.257 --> 07:48.093
We're looking at this winery
with this beautiful courtyard.

07:48.176 --> 07:49.386
-This awesome fountain...
-Yeah.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.096
-Stuffed mushrooms. Elijah.
-What?

07:51.179 --> 07:53.014
You put this baby in me, you
will get me stuffed mushrooms!

07:53.098 --> 07:54.683
Hello, hello. All right.

07:54.766 --> 07:56.559
Hey! There they are.
The couple of the hour.

07:56.643 --> 07:58.436
Uh, this is Leslie.

07:58.520 --> 07:59.771
-KATE: Hi.
-Congratulations, you guys.

07:59.854 --> 08:01.690
-Thank you. Thank you.
-Thank you.

08:01.773 --> 08:03.942
Gosh, you look so familiar.
Have we met?

08:04.025 --> 08:05.485
-Oh, I-I don't think so.
-No.

08:05.568 --> 08:07.112
KATE:
Oh.

08:07.195 --> 08:08.738
-Go on, do it. You can do it.
-Oh.

08:08.822 --> 08:09.948
It's fun.

08:10.990 --> 08:14.285
♪ <i>Like a good neighbor,</i>
<i>State Farm is there!</i> ♪

08:14.369 --> 08:16.454
-Right.
-Of course, yeah.

08:16.538 --> 08:18.373
Of course.
You're the-the State Farm girl.

08:18.456 --> 08:19.666
-LESLIE: Yes!
-Yes.

08:19.749 --> 08:22.002
-(laughter)
-PHILIP: So nice to meet you.

08:22.085 --> 08:24.087
She's not making
the family photo.

08:24.170 --> 08:25.672
-Don't even...
-What are you talking about?

08:25.755 --> 08:26.673
There's some potential there.

08:26.756 --> 08:27.882
-No?
-There was potential

08:27.966 --> 08:29.551
with the Verizon girl,
the iPhone girl,

08:29.634 --> 08:30.802
with the condom
commercial girl...

08:30.885 --> 08:32.554
The condom commercial girl.

08:32.637 --> 08:34.514
Yeah, maybe you're right.
Maybe no-no photo.

08:34.597 --> 08:36.266
-Yeah. Right.
-Yeah.

08:36.349 --> 08:39.561
(speaking indistinctly)

08:40.854 --> 08:42.522
Hey, are you okay?

08:42.605 --> 08:44.607
Uh...

08:44.691 --> 08:46.651
I told you she was going
to be here with her husband.

08:46.735 --> 08:50.321
Yeah. Yeah, I'm okay. It's fine.

08:50.405 --> 08:53.783
I-I'm glad you two are
good friends again anyway.

08:53.867 --> 08:54.993
Yeah.

08:55.076 --> 08:56.870
I'm gonna go say hi.

08:59.956 --> 09:01.666
-Hey!
-Hey.

09:01.750 --> 09:03.418
Kate, this spread is next level.

09:03.501 --> 09:05.712
I am burnt out on oysters, which
I didn't think was possible.

09:05.795 --> 09:08.590
But, uh, screw it,
I'm gonna have another one.

09:08.673 --> 09:10.258
-(laughter)
-Good.

09:10.342 --> 09:11.801
I gotta go, Jae Won.

09:11.885 --> 09:14.012
No. No more calls. I'm at
my sister's engagement party.

09:14.095 --> 09:17.349
Bye. Sorry about that.

09:17.432 --> 09:20.101
Donor contributions
for my campaign are up 20%.

09:20.185 --> 09:21.519
He's very excited.

09:23.396 --> 09:25.398
Well, we are excited
to have a future senator

09:25.482 --> 09:26.816
at our engagement party.

09:26.900 --> 09:28.610
RANDALL:
Oh, come on.

09:28.693 --> 09:31.196
Mom, you look beautiful.

09:31.279 --> 09:33.365
Thank you, sweetheart.
You, too.

09:33.448 --> 09:37.577
Oh, I am so, so happy for you.

09:37.660 --> 09:39.204
Thank you.

09:39.287 --> 09:41.289
And for you, too.

09:43.667 --> 09:45.418
Philip.

09:45.502 --> 09:47.462
(exhales)
Thank you.

09:47.545 --> 09:49.673
Yes.

09:49.756 --> 09:51.925
EMCEE:
All right, let's bring Kate
up to the stage.

09:52.008 --> 09:53.843
Oh, if you'll excuse me.

09:53.927 --> 09:56.846
Excuse you where?
W-What's happening?

09:56.930 --> 09:57.889
You'll see.

09:57.972 --> 10:00.725
Oh, boy.

10:00.809 --> 10:02.769
(glasses clinking)

10:04.771 --> 10:09.442
Hi, everyone. Thank you so much
for coming out tonight.

10:09.526 --> 10:11.194
This is really special.

10:11.277 --> 10:14.239
A few years ago,

10:14.322 --> 10:17.242
on an unusually hot day
in Koreatown,

10:17.325 --> 10:20.495
this song changed everything
for us.

10:20.578 --> 10:22.872
So, uh, get your ass
up here, pal. Let's go.

10:22.956 --> 10:24.249
-MAN: Philip!
-WOMAN: Philip!

10:24.332 --> 10:25.500
-KATE: Let's go.
-WOMAN: Come on, Philip.

10:25.583 --> 10:26.710
-KATE: You.
-MAN: Come on, Philip!

10:26.793 --> 10:29.254
-OTHERS: Philip! Philip!
-KATE: Me and you.

10:29.337 --> 10:33.216
I knew it. Ah. All right.

10:35.468 --> 10:36.678
(keyboard playing)

10:36.761 --> 10:39.014
♪ <i>We'll be singing</i> ♪

10:39.097 --> 10:41.182
♪ <i>When we're winning</i> ♪

10:41.266 --> 10:44.686
♪ <i>We'll be singing</i> ♪

10:44.769 --> 10:47.731
♪ <i>I get knocked down,</i>
<i>but I get up again</i> ♪

10:47.814 --> 10:50.316
♪ <i>You're never gonna</i>
<i>keep me down</i> ♪

10:50.400 --> 10:53.028
♪ <i>I get knocked down,</i>
<i>but I get up again</i> ♪

10:53.111 --> 10:54.029
♪ <i>You're never gonna keep</i> ♪

10:54.112 --> 10:55.030
Everybody!

